Description: IQID is your Digital Internet ID that you share with others to build trust and transparency between buyers and sellers
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: What is IQID? IQID is your Digital Internet ID that you share with others to build trust and transparency between buyers and sellers.  We do this by building transparency between two unknown parties on the internet by creating a shareable “IQID Trust Score” based on your verified government ID and social network presence. IQID verifies your government identity (Passport, Driver’s License, ID Card) to bring trust to the anonymous internet and validate you as a legitimate person.  You create your own unique, private profile web page with your identity on it, then share it with another person via text message before you do a transaction. This helps make buying and selling easier by seeing the person’s real name, their IQID Trust Score and social network status. IQID is perfect for the growing audience of P2P (Person to Person) meetings, O2O (Online to Offline) transactions and aids in the trusted sharing of valuable resources (cars, apartments, equipment) with your local neighbor or with the merchant around the world. The IQID platform is currently Android, Web compatible and is ideal for selling your car, renting an apartment, bridging online buyers and sellers together or for helping small businesses facilitate direct transactions.

Description: Old floor leveling
Full Description: Address: 149 S Briggs St Erie, CO 80516 Description: We offer full-service under board installation services for homes and businesses throughout Colorado. Trust your next under board installation to a team that has years of experience perfecting floors throughout Denver. When you are tiling a home or business floor, you need to be sure that every element is perfectly aligned. Far too often, shoddy tilers skip steps and one of the most common is that of underboarding (also known as underlayment).  At Expert Touch Tiling, we know that every detail matters. That is why we have made a habit of perfecting the details like underboards so you never have to worry about shifting or sagging. Learn more about underboarding and what we can do for you. Underboards or underlayment are the final piece of the puzzle in your floor’s foundations. Usually installed on top of subflooring, underlayment can be used to stabilize or level out floors before they are finished with materials like hardwood, tile, or laminate. Because underboards are usually used to correct or finalize a subfloor before tiling or finish materials are placed, it is essential that they are installed to angle-perfect precision. These last layers are one of the key pieces to keeping your floors sturdy, straight, and non-squeaky for the long-haul, so don’t go it alone!
